Introduction

(todo - personal introduction) Andreas - Psychology inspired Human-Factors researcher.

My Project

Online job advertisements are now being used around the world as a source of insight into the nature of our rapidly changing labour markets. However, before we can determine what inferences are appropriate form the data and used it for informing decisions about labour markets, is is importatnt to check the quality and potential bias of this datasource. Our goal is to understand the strengths and weaknesses of online job advertisements as a source of information about changing demand for workers and skills. We here present one example of this data characterisation process: a comparison of two online job ad datasets: Adzuna Australia (a dataset we used in the wider project) database and the Internet Vacancy Index (a dataset collected by The Department of Jobs and Small Business). Both of these dataset collect online job ads from different sources (online job ads portals).
